<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-Ohtz41HGuq67CPnA0_wcJA" name="sys_uc_priority_list,_gpdNwJfxEd6u7McLcbxIEQ" guid="-Ohtz41HGuq67CPnA0_wcJA" changeDate="2009-11-18T14:32:51.234-0800" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The overall priority could be driven by a number of factors, for example:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The benefit to the stakeholders&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Architectural impact&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Risks to be mitigated&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Each use case should be assigned a value for each criterion relevant to the project and enough information should be&#xD;
    provided in support for prioritizing and partitioning the system use cases.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To help with managing and scheduling of the overall effort based on the most critical and/or important use cases.</purpose>
  <impactOfNotHaving>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Without this artifact, in a use-case driven development environment,&amp;nbsp;mitigating risks and managing the overall&#xD;
    effort becomes a very difficult task,&amp;nbsp;as the main&amp;nbsp;source for taking decisions around scheduling and resource&#xD;
    allocation&amp;nbsp;would be&amp;nbsp;missing.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p></impactOfNotHaving>
  <representationOptions>This list could be maintained in a document or spreadsheet. In some cases, it could also captured in a modeling tool.</representationOptions>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
